# Shadow Conventions

Three named CSS classes cover every surface. Never use inline shadow values for these patterns.

| Surface | Class | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| In-page content card | `card-elevated` | White cards on the `#F1F5FD` / `#F7FAFF` page surface |
| Sticky/fixed footer bar | `footer-elevated` | Fixed bar separating footer from scrollable content |
| Bottom sheet panel | `sheet-elevated` | Modal sheets rising from the bottom |

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<div className="rounded-2xl bg-white card-elevated px-4 py-4">...</div>
<div className="fixed bottom-0 ... footer-elevated">...</div>
<div className="... rounded-t-[24px] bg-white sheet-elevated ...">...</div>

// ❌ BAD — inline shadow values drift over time
<div className="rounded-2xl bg-white shadow-[0_4px_14px_rgba(18,18,18,0.04)] ...">
<div className="fixed bottom-0 shadow-[0_-4px_6px_0_rgba(54,53,76,0.08)] ...">
```

# Concierge Artifact Card Spacing

## Stacking multiple artifact cards

When an artifact contains more than one card stacked vertically, use `gap-4` (16px):

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
  <AmountReceivedCard ... />
  <ShimmerInfoCard ... />
</div>

// ❌ BAD — gap-3 is too tight between distinct cards
<div className="flex flex-col gap-3">...</div>
```

## Internal rows within a single card

Rows inside a card (e.g., `<dl>`, amount rows) use `gap-3` (12px) or smaller — do not change these.
